Abia State Governor, Dr. Okezie Ikpeazu has said his administration would not deviate from ideals and goals of founding fathers of the state just as he promised to complete process of a total handover of public primary schools to their original owners.  The governor although admitted at a Thanksgiving Service at the Mata Dei Cathedral, Umuahia yesterday that the state was passing through a phase in its history which required God’s grace. He solicited for residents’ unflinching support of the people to wade through. He assured the state that hi administration was committed to fulfilling its campaign promises.  Ikpeazu, who spoke through his deputy, Sir Ude Okochukwu thanked Abians for their support and cooperation as well as security operatives in the state for the prevailing peace in the state, noting that harmony and peaceful co-existence would continue to uphold Abia before God.